parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine oil drops on the exhaust manifold

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or stranding.
Engine hesitation and stalling can cause loss of power, accidents, or stranding.
Engine component failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or stranding.
Excessive engine oil consumption can cause engine damage and lead to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: Engine uses excessive oil between oil changes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power loss and failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: power brakes and power steering failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor wear can cause vibration when applying brakes, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: brake pedal nearly goes to the floor
rumbling noise from the back brakes
especially when backing up and coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS system failure can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake caliper failure can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake caliper upper retaining bolt falls out
brake caliper lodges against and locks up the wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: all interior and external lights dim

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: check engine light comes on and then goes off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
difficulty turning to the left or right
unusual noise or vibration while steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
difficulty turning to the left or right
unusual noise or vibration while steering
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cradle can cause the steering system to malfunction, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
difficulty turning to the left or right
unusual noise or vibration while steering
the engine cradle bolts shear off.
